net.sourceforge.earticleast.app
Class AbstractManipulator

java.lang.Object
  net.sourceforge.earticleast.app.AbstractManipulator
Direct Known Subclasses:
ASTDirectManipulator, ASTRewriteBasedManipulator
public abstract class AbstractManipulator
extends java.lang.Object

The base class of the two AST manipulators. The implementations are ASTDirectManipulator and ASTRewriteBasedManipulator. Both subclasses lead to the same result, using different methods to change an AST.

Project page: http://sourceforge.net/projects/earticleast

Author:
Thomas Kuhn

manipulate

public void manipulate(org.eclipse.jdt.core.dom.CompilationUnit unit,
                       java.util.Collection<VariableBindingManager> managers)
Calls for every local variable handled by managers the methods deleteOldVariableDeclaration(VariableBindingManager) and addNewVariableDeclaration(VariableBindingManager). This "moves" the variable declaration statement to its intended place.

Parameters:
unit - the compilation unit that has to be manipulated
managers - all variable binding managers for unit

createNewVariableDeclarationStatement

protected org.eclipse.jdt.core.dom.VariableDeclarationStatement createNewVariableDeclarationStatement(VariableBindingManager manager,
                                                                                                      org.eclipse.jdt.core.dom.AST ast)
Creates a new VariableDeclarationStatement. As initializer figures a copy of the initializer retrieved from the variable binding manager. The variable name will be a copy of the variable declaration fragment name returned by the variable binding manager.

Parameters:
